<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,293,804]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,317,517,543]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
The name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[460,580,517,542]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="iridis" variety="levantinus">
<emphasis box="[460,580,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">levantinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”was employed as a new variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[995,1126,517,542]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis box="[995,1126,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Petri" box="[1171,1325,517,543]" pageId="18" pageNumber="21" refString="Petri, K. (1904 b) Bestimmungs-Tabelle der mir bekannt gewordenen Arten der Gattung Lixus Fab. aus Europa und den angrenzenden Gebieten. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 23 (9): 183 - 198." type="journal article" year="1904" yearSuffix="b">
Petri (
<number box="[1241,1302,517,543]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1904.0">1904</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
“ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Größer, glänzander, Halsschild sehr stark und tief runzlig-grubig skulptiert, der Rüssel dünner und scheinbar länger, Flügeldeckenspitzen ziemlich lang. 
<collectingCountry box="[591,688,592,617]" name="Iran" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Persien</collectingCountry>
, Anatolien, Rumelien, Olymp, Sizilien.
</emphasis>
”. According to 
<collectionCode box="[1366,1437,592,618]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">ICZN</collectionCode>
article 
<number box="[236,295,629,655]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="45.6">45.6</number>
. 
<number box="[299,317,629,655]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
., 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[337,571,629,655]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis box="[337,476,629,654]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus iridis</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Petri" authorityName="Petri" box="[580,802,629,655]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="iridis" variety="levantinus">
v. 
<emphasis box="[610,735,629,654]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">levantinus</emphasis>
Petri
</taxonomicName>
is considered at the subspecific rank. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="18" pageNumber="21" refString="Heyden, L. von, E. Reitter &amp; J. Weise. (1906) Catalogus Coleopterorum Europae, Caucasi et Armeniae Rossicae. Ed. II. Paskau, V + 774 pp." type="book">
Heyden et al. (
<number box="[159,220,666,692]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1906.0">1906</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was the first to place this name in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName box="[835,969,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis box="[835,969,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Winkler" box="[1134,1315,666,692]" pageId="18" pageNumber="21" refString="Winkler, A. (1932) Catalogus coleopterorum regionis palearcticae. Pars 12: 1393 - 1520. A. Winkler, Wien." type="journal article" year="1932">
Winkler (
<number box="[1246,1307,666,692]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1932.0">1932</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Csiki" pageId="18" pageNumber="20" refString="Csiki, E. (1934) Coleopterorum Catalogus auspiciis et auxilio W. Junk editus a S. Schenkling. Pars 134. Curculionidae: subfam. Cleoninae. Junk, Berlin, 152 p." type="book" year="1934">
Csiki (
<number box="[160,225,704,730]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1934.0">1934</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. This is the only available 
<typeStatus box="[555,647,704,730]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">syntype</typeStatus>
in Reitter’s collection fitting the description. It is not 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1429,704,729]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis box="[1293,1429,704,729]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and thus a new synonymy is proposed here: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hochhuth, 1847" authorityName="Hochhuth" authorityYear="1847" box="[705,1123,741,767]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nordmanni">
<emphasis box="[705,914,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus nordmanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hochhuth" box="[924,1123,741,767]" pageId="18" pageNumber="20" refString="Hochhuth, I. H. (1847) Enumeration der Russelkafer welche von Baron Maximilian von Chaudoir und von Baron A. v. Gotsch auf ihren Reisen im Kaukasus und in Transcaucasien im Jahre 1845 gesammelt werden; nebst Beschreibung der neuentdeckten Arten. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 20 (2): 448 - 587." type="journal article" year="1847">
Hochhuth, 
<number box="[1062,1123,741,767]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1847.0">1847</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[1168,1406,741,767]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis box="[1168,1310,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus iridis</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Petri, 1904" authorityName="Petri" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="iridis" status="syn. n." variety="levantinus">
v. 
<emphasis box="[151,272,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">levantinus</emphasis>
Petri, 
<number box="[348,407,778,804]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[414,495,778,804]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[414,495,778,804]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
].
</paragraph>
